1195
01:12:19,063 --> 01:12:22,423
Dear God! Where were you
all this time?

1196
01:12:22,983 --> 01:12:25,703
It wasn't my story.
There was an accident...

1197
01:12:29,222 --> 01:12:33,007
Where were you?

1198
01:12:37,143 --> 01:12:38,623
Everett?

1199
01:12:40,343 --> 01:12:41,743
Warden.

1200
01:12:42,743 --> 01:12:45,382
You know, people come
in here, the press.

1201
01:12:45,623 --> 01:12:49,743
Prisoners tell them things.
All kind of heart-wrenching things.

1202
01:12:50,263 --> 01:12:51,858
And the next day in the paper,

1203
01:12:51,859 --> 01:12:54,462
we're the one come off
sounding like hard guys.

1204
01:12:55,063 --> 01:12:57,022
It can get pretty frustrating, is all.

1205
01:12:57,302 --> 01:12:58,863
Yeah, of course.

1206
01:12:59,143 --> 01:13:01,702
We have to do what
the state tells us to do.

1207
01:13:02,822 --> 01:13:04,022
Makes it a little tough on us...

1208
01:13:04,302 --> 01:13:07,742
...if we show up in the paper
as bloody murderers or anything like that.

1209
01:13:09,343 --> 01:13:12,223
Yeah, I understand. Completely.

1210
01:13:12,702 --> 01:13:14,022
Knew you would.

1211
01:13:16,222 --> 01:13:19,422
You know these things go through
all kind of trials and appeals...

1212
01:13:19,702 --> 01:13:21,582
...before they get to us.

1213
01:13:22,822 --> 01:13:25,462
There's no use trying to figure out
who's naughty or who's nice...

1214
01:13:25,702 --> 01:13:28,903
...and then come sliding down the
chimney like a hero.

1215
01:13:29,542 --> 01:13:31,263
Not on execution day.

1216
01:13:33,183 --> 01:13:34,902
You're not Santa Claus.

1217
01:13:37,462 --> 01:13:39,743
No such thing as Santa Claus.

1218
01:13:48,302 --> 01:13:49,222
Warden?

1219
01:13:51,982 --> 01:13:53,782
You're not really sure, are you?

1220
01:14:00,782 --> 01:14:02,622
You drive safe now.

